Remains of the Palace of King Nissanka Malla
Remains of palace of Nissanka Malla lies behind the current Polonnaruwa Rest House along with the
. This place has been probably built mainly with bricks during the reign of King Nissanka Malla (1187-1196) thus there is only very little of this palace complex remains.
Historians believe that the palace would have been a two storied building with top floor made of out of wood.
This palace would have been a dwarf compared the palace of King Maha Parakramabahu  (1153-1186) which had seven stories and 1000 rooms which lies about 1 km from this location.
